<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,1909,2006]" lastBlockId="7.[151,1437,151,896]" lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="386" pageId="6" pageNumber="385">
Body yellowish brown. Eyes brownish; occiput with 
<number box="[799,813,1910,1934]" pageId="6" pageNumber="385" value="1.0">1</number>
semicircular transverse black brown stripe, which split in middle, outer area with 
<number box="[450,464,1946,1970]" pageId="6" pageNumber="385" value="1.0">1</number>
pair of short black stripes (
<figureCitation box="[775,843,1945,1970]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1781,1803]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,195,1757]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1436,195,1757]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 6. Apotrechus trilobus Bian &amp; Shi sp. nov.: A, H. head in frontal view; B – C, I – J. head and pronotum: B, I. dorsal view, C, J. lateral view; D – F, K. apex of abdomen: D. dorsal view, E, K. lateral view, F. apico-lateral view; G, L. subgenital plate in ventral view; A – G. male, holotype; H – L. female, paratype." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/250086/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="385">
Fig. 
<number box="[828,843,1945,1970]" pageId="6" pageNumber="385" value="6.0">6</number>
</figureCitation>
B); fastigium verticis with 
<number box="[1147,1161,1946,1970]" pageId="6" pageNumber="385" value="3.0">3</number>
small black spots; frons with 
<number box="[207,221,1982,2006]" pageId="6" pageNumber="385" value="1.0">1</number>
pair of vertical black stripes beneath antennal foveolae and 
<number box="[891,905,1982,2006]" pageId="6" pageNumber="385" value="1.0">1</number>
vertical black stripe in middle (
<figureCitation box="[1259,1326,1981,2006]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1781,1803]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,195,1757]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1436,195,1757]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 6. Apotrechus trilobus Bian &amp; Shi sp. nov.: A, H. head in frontal view; B – C, I – J. head and pronotum: B, I. dorsal view, C, J. lateral view; D – F, K. apex of abdomen: D. dorsal view, E, K. lateral view, F. apico-lateral view; G, L. subgenital plate in ventral view; A – G. male, holotype; H – L. female, paratype." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/250086/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="385">
Fig. 
<number box="[1311,1326,1981,2006]" pageId="6" pageNumber="385" value="6.0">6</number>
</figureCitation>
A); apical part of mandibles black; inner margin of antennal socket, basal area of scape and pedicel, and basal articles of flagellum black brown, the other part of flagellum lighter. Pronotum with black margins, in the disc with 
<number box="[1422,1436,188,212]" pageId="7" pageNumber="386" value="1.0">1</number>
longitudinal black stripe. Mesonotum, metanotum and first abdominal tergite with black margins and a median black stripes separately. Apical area of fore and middle femora black brown, basal area and apical area of tibiae black and all spines on hind legs black brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,151,896]" pageId="7" pageNumber="386">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,293,332,357]" pageId="7" pageNumber="386">Female.</emphasis>
Appearance is similar to male. Subgenital plate short, basally broad, apical half slightly narrowing, basal margin excavate, lateral margin triangular expanded, posterior margin slightly projecting in middle (
<figureCitation box="[1337,1404,367,392]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1781,1803]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,195,1757]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1436,195,1757]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 6. Apotrechus trilobus Bian &amp; Shi sp. nov.: A, H. head in frontal view; B – C, I – J. head and pronotum: B, I. dorsal view, C, J. lateral view; D – F, K. apex of abdomen: D. dorsal view, E, K. lateral view, F. apico-lateral view; G, L. subgenital plate in ventral view; A – G. male, holotype; H – L. female, paratype." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/250086/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="386">
Fig. 
<number box="[1389,1404,367,392]" pageId="7" pageNumber="386" value="6.0">6</number>
</figureCitation>
L). Ovipositor short, dorsal and ventral margins smooth, base stout, narrowing, apical half curved upwards, apex obtuse.
</paragraph>
