<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="386" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,151,896]" pageId="7" pageNumber="386">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,692,717]" pageId="7" pageNumber="386">Remarks.</emphasis>
The new species is very similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Liu &amp; Bi, 2008" authorityName="Liu &amp; Bi" authorityYear="2008" box="[728,1117,692,717]" class="Insecta" family="Haglidae" genus="Apotrechus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="386" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fallax">
<emphasis box="[728,927,692,716]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="386">Apotrechus fallax</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Liu" box="[936,1117,692,717]" pageId="7" pageNumber="386" refString="Liu, X. - W. &amp; Bi, W. - X. (2008) Two new species of the genus Apotrechus (Orthoptera: Stenopelmatidae: Gryllacrinae). Entomotaxonomia, 30 (1), 11 - 14. [in Chinese with English summary]" type="journal article" year="2008">
Liu &amp; Bi, 
<number box="[1058,1117,692,716]" pageId="7" pageNumber="386" value="2008.0">2008</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, but differs in: frons with 
<number box="[1422,1436,692,716]" pageId="7" pageNumber="386" value="1.0">1</number>
vertical black stripe in middle; lateral lobes of male subgenital plate with 
<number box="[1027,1041,728,752]" pageId="7" pageNumber="386" value="1.0">1</number>
pair of apically processes, which digitate in apico-lateral view; lateral margin of female subgenital plate triangular expanded in middle, posterior margin slightly projecting in middle.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="386" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,151,896]" pageId="7" pageNumber="386">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,836,861]" pageId="7" pageNumber="386">Etymology.</emphasis>
The name of the new species is derived from the triangular expansion of female subgenital plate in middle area.
</paragraph>
